  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Sources of Water in Schools for Syrian Refugee Families in Jordan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mercy Corps is upgrading water and sanitation facilities and installing rain water catchment systems in schools in Irbid, Northern Jordan with support from United States Agency for International Development (USAID) and United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR). A partnership with The Lifeplus Foundation will enable us to reach 1,650 Syrian refugee and vulnerable Jordanian children and staff in three schools with sustainable mechanisms of supplying water. Rainwater catchment systems collect water from the roof, channeling it to a permanent concrete cistern and can hold 80 &#x2013; 100 cubic meters of water.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Refugees</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal is provide access to clean and safe drinking water for 1,650 Syrian refugee and host community children and staff in three schools in Northern Jordan.</narrative>
  </description>
